Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["A note on dataset normalization", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.635883990517587*^9, 3.6358840177941475`*^9}, {
  3.6358843920845556`*^9, 3.635884394625701*^9}}],

Cell["\<\
It is typically suggested that the dataset be normalized/rescaled before \
running LDA on it. However, normalization of all values to the interval (0,1) \
actually throws away information about the different dynamic ranges of \
different variables. If any normalization must be done, just in order to deal \
with numbers of the same order of magnitude, then Standardize is the most \
appropriate.

However, if the LDA is run on the normalized dataset, the eigenvectors cannot \
be properly used to transform new non-normalized data!! Also, new \
non-normalized data cannot be normalized in the same way that the original \
training set was, unless we record and transfer the maximum and minimum \
values used in the normalization of the original training set. This is \
probably a bad idea and a serious complication, at least at the initial level. 

In the function below normalization is turned OFF by default, i.e. running \
LDA with no switch will assume that the data should not be normalized, and \
that the dataset has headers. If this assumption is incorrect, and in fact \
the dataset doesn\[CloseCurlyQuote]t have headers, then the first row of the \
dataset will be discarded. Although this assumption may lead to wasting a \
sample replicate from the first group, it is still safer than assuming that \
no headers are present: in fact, in that case the headers will hang the \
calculation and one has to quit the kernel to recover.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6358840207663174`*^9, 3.6358843881103287`*^9}, {
  3.635959854026927*^9, 3.6359598552649975`*^9}, {3.635959969094508*^9, 
  3.635959981622225*^9}}]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Functional implementation of LDA", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.635864911201313*^9, 3.635864929405354*^9}, {
  3.635884403942234*^9, 3.635884408720507*^9}}],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Things that need to be done:", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6358844131307592`*^9, 3.6358844259074903`*^9}, {
  3.6375137196284943`*^9, 3.637513721219697*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "check whether to normalize full data set column-wise\ngenerate a series of \
subsets by using the labels in the first column to gather data by its class\n\
calculate within class scatter for each class (Swi) and sum them up to give \
total within-class scatter (Sw): ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", "sets"], 
    RowBox[{
     UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
      RowBox[{"samples", " ", "in", " ", "a", " ", "set"}]], 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"x", "-", 
        SubscriptBox[
         OverscriptBox["x", "_"], "set"]}], ")"}], "\[CenterDot]", 
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"x", "-", 
         SubscriptBox[
          OverscriptBox["x", "_"], "set"]}], ")"}], "T"]}]}]}], 
   TraditionalForm]]],
 "\ncalculate between class scatter (Sb): ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", "sets"], 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SubscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["x", "_"], "set"], "-", 
       SubscriptBox["\[Mu]", "global"]}], ")"}], "\[CenterDot]", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox[
         OverscriptBox["x", "_"], "set"], "-", 
        SubscriptBox["\[Mu]", "global"]}], ")"}], "T"]}]}], TraditionalForm]]],
 "\nsolve eigensystem of matrix ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["Sw", 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]]],
 "\[CenterDot]",
 "Sb\nplot transformed dataset in 2D with tooltips\nreturn eigensystem"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6358649331855707`*^9, 3.635865063593029*^9}, {
  3.635867006829176*^9, 3.6358670630373907`*^9}, {3.6358839819901*^9, 
  3.6358839862363424`*^9}, {3.635884448595788*^9, 3.6358845093632636`*^9}, {
  3.635884548852522*^9, 3.6358848287055287`*^9}}]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Implementation", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.6358844396292753`*^9, 3.635884442574444*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Remove", "[", "lda", "]"}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"Options", "[", "lda", "]"}], "=", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"applyfunc", "\[Rule]", "Identity"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"output", "\[Rule]", "\"\<2DL\>\""}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"ellipsoidcolor", "\[Rule]", "Automatic"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"swapaxes", "\[Rule]", "False"}]}], "}"}]}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"lda", "::", "usage"}], "=", 
   "\"\<lda[dataset] carries out Linear Discriminant Analysis on dataset and \
returns the transformed data as factor scores (default), or other numerical / \
graphical results. Each row of dataset should contain a sample; the first \
column contains the class identifier for that sample.\\nOptions:\\napplyfunc \
(Identity (default), Standardize, Rescale, ...)\\noutput (\\\"scores\\\", \
\\\"vartable\\\", \\\"eigenvectors\\\", \\\"eigensystem\\\", \\\"2D\\\" (= 2D \
score plot), \\\"2DL\\\" (= 2D score and loading plots, default), \\\"3D\\\", \
\\\"3DL\\\")\\nswapaxes (default = {False,False}).\>\""}], 
  ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"lda", "::", "outputoptions"}], "=", 
   "\"\<The value `1` is not a valid plotting option. Valid options are: \
\\\"eigenvectors\\\" (default), \\\"eigensystem\\\", \\\"vartable\\\", \\\"2D\
\\\", \\\"3D\\\".\>\""}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"lda", "::", "swapaxesnotboolean"}], "=", 
   "\"\<The value `1` is not a valid swapaxes option. Use only True / False \
or combinations thereof.\>\""}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"lda", "::", "swapaxeslength"}], "=", 
   "\"\<The value `1` given for the swapaxes option is not valid. Acceptable \
values are a single True / False, to be applied to all axes, or a list \
containing as many True/False values as there are axes in the requested plot.\
\>\""}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"lda", "::", "ellcolor"}], "=", 
    "\"\<The value `1` for the ellipsoidcolor option is not valid. Acceptable \
values are: Automatic, True, False. Automatic settings were used.\>\""}], 
   ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
  "\[IndentingNewLine]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"lda", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"matrix_", "/;", 
      RowBox[{"MatrixQ", "[", "matrix", "]"}]}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"OptionsPattern", "[", "]"}]}], "]"}], ":=", 
   RowBox[{"Module", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
        "the", " ", "definition", " ", "below", " ", "is", " ", "important"}],
         ",", " ", 
        RowBox[{"althouhg", " ", "it", " ", "looks", " ", 
         RowBox[{"silly", "!"}]}]}], "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
      RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
        "If", " ", "one", " ", "used", " ", "matrix", " ", "directly", " ", 
         "in", " ", "the", " ", "function", " ", "body"}], ",", " ", 
        RowBox[{
        "the", " ", "VALUE", " ", "of", " ", "matrix", " ", "would", " ", 
         "be", " ", "substituted"}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
      RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
       RowBox[{"everywhere", " ", "BEFORE", " ", "any", " ", "further", " ", 
        RowBox[{"evaluation", ".", " ", "the"}], " ", "name", " ", "of", " ", 
        "the", " ", "pattern", " ", "is", " ", "not", " ", "a", " ", "proper",
         " ", 
        RowBox[{"variable", "!!"}]}], " ", "*)"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
      RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
       RowBox[{
       "This", " ", "is", " ", "the", " ", "reason", " ", "why", " ", "the", 
        " ", "standardization", " ", "in", " ", "place", " ", "did", " ", 
        "not", " ", "work", " ", "before"}], " ", "*)"}], 
      "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"dataset", "=", "matrix"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
       "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
       RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
        RowBox[{"other", " ", "local", " ", "variables"}], "*)"}], 
       "\[IndentingNewLine]", "hascolumnheaders", ",", "columnheaderlist", 
       ",", "classlist", ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "partitioneddata", ",", 
       "transformeddata", ",", "labeledtransformed", ",", "partitionedscores",
        ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "grandmean", ",", "clustermeans", ",", 
       "Swi", ",", "Sw", ",", "Sb", ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "eigenvals", 
       ",", "eigenvecs", ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "plotdata", ",", 
       "readyforplot", ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "ellipsoids2D", ",", 
       "coloredellipsoids2D", ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "ellipsoids3D", ",",
        "coloredellipsoids3D"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", "}"}], ",", 
     "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{"(*", " ", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
       "if", " ", "column", " ", "headers", " ", "are", " ", "present"}], ",",
        " ", 
       RowBox[{
       "extract", " ", "them", " ", "and", " ", "assign", " ", "them", " ", 
